.TH GAT-SEARCH 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-search \- search worktrees, optionally through fzf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat search
.RI [ query ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B gat find
.RI [ query ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Builds a stable, tab-separated feed of
.IR branch <TAB> state <TAB> path .
By default it pipes the feed through
.BR fzf (1)
for interactive selection; the selected worktree can be switched to (with shell
integration), printed, or opened in tmux. With
.B \-\-print
or
.B \-\-no\-fzf
it emits the raw feed for use with
.BR awk (1),
.BR grep (1),
or other tools.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-print
Print the tab-separated feed instead of invoking fzf.
.TP
.B \-\-path
Print only the selected path.
.TP
.B \-\-tmux
Open the selected worktree's tmux session.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-fzf
Do not invoke fzf; print the feed.
.TP
.B \-\-full
Include dirty/merged checks in the feed.
.TP
.B \-\-fast
Skip expensive checks (default).
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json|shell"
Output format for the selected item.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat search
gat search login
gat search \-\-print | awk \-F '\\t' '$2 ~ /dirty/ { print $1 }'
gat search \-\-tmux
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-list (1),
.BR gat\-switch (1)
